President Barack Obama has announced his intention to nominate Ajit Varadaraj Pai for the position of Commissioner at the Federal Communications Commission (FCC). Pai is currently a Partner in the Litigation Department of Jenner & Block LLP. Prior to this, he worked in various roles at the FCC, including Deputy General Counsel and Associate General Counsel. He has also served as Chief Counsel to the U.S. Senate Judiciary Committee's Subcommittee on the Constitution, Civil Rights, and Property Rights, as well as Senior Counsel at the Office of Legal Policy at the U.S. Department of Justice. Pai has also worked at Verizon Communications Inc. as Associate General Counsel. He began his career as a law clerk to Judge Martin L.C. Feldman and then as a trial attorney in the Telecommunications Task Force at the U.S. Department of Justice's Antitrust Division. Pai holds a B.A. from Harvard University and a J.D. from the University of Chicago.